"{\"content\":{\"body\":\"We appreciate you being here early, and thank you for your patience as we improve Mirror. Thereâ€™s a lot of work to do, and with that are certain compromises.\\n\\nIn this spirit, weâ€™ve decided to implement a plain text editor with Markdown formatting, similar to pro favorites like [iA Writer](https://ia.net/writer). This is in contrast to a WYSIWYG editor, like Notion. We came to this conclusion after speaking with a number of our favorite writers who require an easy way to go from their favorite writing app (like iA Writer) to Mirror.\\n\\nAs such Mirror supports all of markdown, plus a few special extras. For an extensive Markdown formatting guide, take a look at [Daring Fireball](https://daringfireball.net/projects/markdown/syntax). We aim to implement support for copy-and-paste between tools like Google Docs and platforms such as Medium. All in time ðŸ˜Œ\\n\\n*Note*: There are already plans to deprecate this simplistic editor in favor of something more dynamic. These plans have no impact on the writing you do todayâ€”weâ€™ll take care of migrating you when the time comes.\\n\\nLetâ€™s $WRITE.\\n\\n## Media Blocks\\n\\nCreating a media embed on Mirror is extremely simple:\\n\\n1. Create a new line of text.\\n2. Add a link to anything.\\n3. Insert a line break.\\n\\nIt looks like this:\\n\\n```markdown\\nThe 90-minute presentation essentially demonstrated almost all the fundamental elements of modern personal computing:\\n\\n[The Mother of All Demos](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yJDv-zdhzMY)\\n\\nEngelbart's presentation was the first to publicly demonstrate all of these elements in a single system.\\n```\\n\\nAs youâ€™d guess, this creates a Youtube embed:\\n\\n[The Mother of All Demos](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FCiBUawCawo)\\n\\nSimple, right? Weâ€™ve decided to parse basic linksâ€”as opposed to introducing Mirror specific syntaxâ€”to ensure portability. If the markdown is rendered with Mirror you will see Media Blocks. If anywhere else, youâ€™ll see a simple plain text link. There are a number of integrations, and weâ€™re adding more every week.\\n\\nThis is almost embarrassingly simple, but below is a comprehensive list.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Link Previews\\n\\n```md\\n[Mirror](https://mirror.xyz)\\n```\\n\\nMirror displays a progressively enhanced preview of all links based on the universal standard of [OpenGraph tags](https://ogp.me). This is the same standard you see on Twitter and Facebook.\\n\\n[Mirror](https://mirror.xyz)\\n\\n### Twitter\\n\\n```md\\n[Mirrorâ€™s first tweet](https://twitter.com/viamirror/status/1325856116748726273)\\n```\\n\\n[Mirrorâ€™s first tweet](https://twitter.com/viamirror/status/1325856116748726273)\\n\\n### Youtube\\n\\n```md\\n[Design jam on Youtube](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=geRPXByWV2U&feature=youtu.be)\\n```\\n\\n[Design jam on Youtube](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=geRPXByWV2U&feature=youtu.be)\\n\\n---\\n\\nAre we missing an integration youâ€™d like to see? Please donâ€™t hesitate to [say hello](d@mirror.xyz)!\",\"timestamp\":1610602082,\"title\":\"Formatting Guide\",\"publication\":\"jktest\"},\"digest\":\"0_UcAN6srUBe_cOTIsc0QA2pGVQrnrz22OAy29V6YYE\",\"authorship\":{\"contributor\":\"0x841fF85B6873d7bfB712C8f7A347C774355b6EC3\",\"signingKey\":\"{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\\":\\\"D1Nn9IpEf0chYibcqyEM8fB8CHFqq6rMbIYwnOkCxDA\\\",\\\"y\\\":\\\"z6c6bKX6AOAv9yhlnT3b4QeGXaxhPpbIhO4uOpD4oLU\\\"}\",\"signature\":\"0BS04-boJ47RCRzaEZHuXDEy3ONuPfoG8hp7hwFyX9_t9hyy63bZlSvWDxaMr6C087QhcWDLAXkJk8qEOMJiwg\",\"signingKeySignature\":\"0x941ba0ed82249496350320f822e1ba02977fea61efb3faa9497970fe4831b4990ce47f13da9d5baaf32aa320c34d86ac76f56c09e40cfa646cfd889094b5b8e61b\",\"signingKeyMessage\":\"I authorize the publication of articles on jktest.mirror.xyz from this device using:\\n{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\